children.subject: It just expanded a while ago.

history.content:
The latest information I've heard on this: some (but not all) summer classes are willing to continue expanding, but we can't promise anything publicly because the expansion depends on approval from the department (e.g. allocating additional funding, expanding beyond room capacities, etc.). If a class is willing to expand and everything checks out, you'll find out by seeing that it expanded in the enrollment system.

For CS 70 specifically, it looks like there's 30ish people waitlisted, so even if they don't expand again, you might have a good chance of being enrolled off the waitlist from people dropping.
